This school project implements a frustum algorithm in OpenGL and C++. It
contains a town and a spotlight and on the second camera it is shown what
objects are seen by the spotlight source(first camera).

Keyboard inputs:
- Translate left, right: i/u; up, down: y,t; forward, backward: p,o
- Rotate on right direction: g,f; on up direction: j,h; on forward direction:
l,k
- Switch between the two cameras: c
   